Verbenol showed the dynamic multi-regime inhibitory activity against the target proteins. It showed the highest binding affinity with the Nor-1 followed by Omt-1 and Vbs. Verbenol formed the hydrogen bonds with ARG52, GLY49, GLY55, and ASN130 in Nor-1, MET225, ARG257, and HIS259 in Omt-1 and with TYR144, and VAL515 in Vbs. Based on the binding energy profile of verbenol, its Ki (inhibition constant) value for each target proteins were calculated following the Eq. (1).1\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
