For investigating the anti-AFB1 efficacy, gradient concentrations of ZOEO (0.1 to 0.6 μl/ml) were separately mixed with the 24.5 ml of SMKY liquid medium (sucrose, 20 g; magnesium sulfate, 0.5 g; potassium nitrate, 3 g; yeast extract, 7 g; and distilled water, 1000 mL) and inoculated with a hundred microliter spore suspension of A. flavus PN-05. After the incubation of 10 ten days, the filtered media was used for the estimation of AFB1 content following the protocol of Prakash et al.55, based on the following formula:\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
